  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Enrolled Nurse/Registered Nurse (Home Care)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide high-quality nursing care and emotional support to patients, ensuring their comfort, safety, and well-being.</li><li>Assess patients’ clinical conditions, monitor vital signs, and administer prescribed medications and treatments accurately.</li><li>Develop, plan, and implement individualized care plans in collaboration with the healthcare team.</li><li>Serve home care clients through hands-on case management and conduct hospital or home visits for client assessments.</li><li>Support the home care team with nursing cases and take up respite assignments when required.</li><li>Advise and guide care staff in managing medical issues or emergencies.</li><li>Communicate effectively with patients’ families, providing timely updates on care and progress.</li><li>Collaborate with colleagues and external community partners to coordinate and manage client care needs.</li><li>Ensure compliance with documentation standards required by the Ministry of Health (MOH) for financial and quality audits.</li><li>Participate in complaint resolution, crisis management, and other ad hoc duties assigned by management.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Nitec/Diploma/Bachelor’s Degree in Nursing.</li><li>Advanced Diploma in Gerontology or Palliative Care is an advantage.</li><li>Must be an Enrolled Nurse or Registered Nurse with the Singapore Nursing Board (SNB) and possess a clean disciplinary record. <em>(Nurses on conditional licenses are not eligible for this role.)</em></li><li>Minimum 2 years of clinical experience.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and comfortable using IT tools in daily work.</li><li>Ability to converse in local dialects will be an added advantage.</li><li>Willingness to perform occasional shift work, particularly to support palliative care patients.</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li>Attractive base salary</li><li>Opportunities for professional training and career development within the organization.</li><li>Health insurance coverage.</li><li>Industry-specific training and mentorship from a highly experienced team.</li><li>Supportive and flexible work environment that encourages innovation and process improvement.</li><li>15 days of annual leave.</li><li>Performance based bonus</li></ul>",
